<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-07-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-07-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="813" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d813">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hunter</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-07-22"><hi rend="italic">July 22,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 270.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            dispatch No. 398, of the 30th ultimo, inclosing a copy of correspondence
                            between you and the minister of foreign affairs of Honduras in relation
                            to the Pears claim.</p>
                        <p>The Department is not disposed to require the punishment of the sentinel
                            who killed Pears. His punishment was not mentioned in instruction No.
                            236 of March 20 last. But delay in responding to the demand for
                            indemnity should not be allowed to pass unnoticed.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>